Azure is a Microsoft’s cloud platform.

Instead of buying your own servers, storage, databases, security tools, and AI tools, you can rent them from Microsoft through the internet.

You use Azure to:
  
  Host websites
  
  Run apps
  
  Store files and data
  
  Create databases
  
  Use AI tools
  
  Manage security
  
  Deploy code
  
  Run virtual computers
  
  Connect company systems together


